Package: ChartKit
Type: Package
Title: Unified Data Visualization Package for Publication-Ready Charts
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("DataConceptz", "R-Vis", email = "contact@dataconceptz.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A comprehensive R package that unifies multiple visualization
    packages (ggplot2, plotly, ggridges, treemapify, ggalluvial, etc.) to provide
    48 chart types ranging from basic to advanced visualizations. Designed for
    creating publication-ready charts with consistent API and colorblind-friendly
    palettes.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
    R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    dplyr,
    magrittr,
    tidyr,
    scales,
    grid,
    gridExtra,
    ggridges,
    ggalluvial,
    treemapify,
    ggraph,
    igraph,
    plotly,
    viridis,
    RColorBrewer,
    cowplot,
    patchwork,
    ggrepel,
    ggforce,
    rlang,
    lubridate
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.0
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/DataConceptz/ChartKit
BugReports: https://github.com/DataConceptz/ChartKit/issues
